cs.RO, cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.SY

This paper deals with predicting the motion of a mobile agent, which is a common problem in robotics applications such as autonomous navigation and tracking. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.RO (Robotics). The paper proposes a novel approach that integrates both kinematic and environmental context into an inverse reinforcement learning framework, which involves machine learning techniques. This suggests that the paper could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), or cs.SY (Systems and Control). Additionally, the paper uses LiDAR statistics to learn feature representations of the environment, which involves computer vision techniques, indicating that it could also belong to cs.CV (Computer Vision).
